label.value: green leaf volatile biosynthetic process

value.value: The chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of volatile molecules emitted from green plants, such as hexenal, hexenol and hexenyl acetate, from linoleic acid or linolenic acid.

label.value: NAD(P)H dehydrogenase complex (plastoquinone)

value.value: Complex that possesses NAD(P)H dehydrogenase (plastoquinone) activity. The complex is one of the components of the electron transport chain. It is involved in electron transport from an unidentified electron donor, possibly NADH, NADPH or ferredoxin(Fd) to the plastoquinone pool.

label.value: lsiRNA processing

value.value: A process leading to the generation of a functional long small interfering RNA (lsiRNA). lsiRNAs are class of siRNAs 30 to 40 nt in length. lsiRNAs are induced by pathogen infection or under specific growth conditions.

label.value: regulation of auxin biosynthetic process

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of auxins, plant hormones that regulate aspects of plant growth.

label.value: positive regulation of auxin biosynthetic process

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways resulting in the formation of auxins, plant hormones that regulate aspects of plant growth.

label.value: regulation of 1-aminocyclopropane-1-carboxylate metabolic process

value.value: Regulation of the chemical reactions and pathways involving 1-aminocyclopropane-1-carboxylate, the anion of 1-aminocyclopropane-1-carboxylic acid, a natural product found in plant tissues. It is a key intermediate in the biosynthesis of ethylene (ethene), a fruit-ripening hormone in plants.

label.value: regulation of cytoplasmic mRNA processing body assembly

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency, or extent of the aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of proteins and RNA molecules to form a cytoplasmic mRNA processing body.

label.value: positive regulation of macromolecule metabolic process

value.value: Any process that increases the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways involving macromolecules, any molecule of high relative molecular mass, the structure of which essentially comprises the multiple repetition of units derived, actually or conceptually, from molecules of low relative molecular mass.

label.value: negative regulation of macromolecule metabolic process

value.value: Any process that decreases the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways involving macromolecules, any molecule of high relative molecular mass, the structure of which essentially comprises the multiple repetition of units derived, actually or conceptually, from molecules of low relative molecular mass.

label.value: positive regulation of cytoplasmic mRNA processing body assembly

value.value: Any process that increases the rate, frequency, or extent of the aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of proteins and RNA molecules to form a cytoplasmic mRNA processing body.

label.value: negative regulation of cytoplasmic mRNA processing body assembly

value.value: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency, or extent of the aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of proteins and RNA molecules to form a cytoplasmic mRNA processing body.

label.value: post-transcriptional regulation of gene expression

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of gene expression after the production of an RNA transcript.

label.value: mRNA localization resulting in post-transcriptional regulation of gene expression

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of gene expression after the production of a mRNA transcript by its transport into, or maintenance in, a specific location within the cell.

label.value: regulation of mRNA stability involved in response to stress

value.value: Any process that modulates the propensity of mRNA molecules to degradation that is part of a change in state or activity of a cell as a result of an exogenous disturbance.

label.value: regulation of cardiac muscle hypertrophy

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of the enlargement or overgrowth of all or part of the heart due to an increase in size (not length) of individual cardiac muscle fibers, without cell division.

label.value: regulation of cardiac muscle adaptation

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, extent or frequency of the process in which cardiac muscle adapts, with consequent modifications to structural and/or functional phenotypes, in response to a stimulus. Stimuli include contractile activity, loading conditions, substrate supply, and environmental factors.

label.value: positive regulation of cardiac muscle hypertrophy

value.value: Any process that increases the rate, frequency or extent of the enlargement or overgrowth of all or part of the heart due to an increase in size (not length) of individual cardiac muscle fibers, without cell division.

label.value: negative regulation of cardiac muscle hypertrophy

value.value: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency or extent of the enlargement or overgrowth of all or part of the heart due to an increase in size (not length) of individual cardiac muscle fibers, without cell division.

label.value: positive regulation of cardiac muscle adaptation

value.value: Any process that increases the rate, extent or frequency of the process in which cardiac muscle adapts, with consequent modifications to structural and/or functional phenotypes, in response to a stimulus. Stimuli include contractile activity, loading conditions, substrate supply, and environmental factors.

label.value: negative regulation of cardiac muscle adaptation

value.value: Any process that decreases the rate, extent or frequency of the process in which cardiac muscle adapts, with consequent modifications to structural and/or functional phenotypes, in response to a stimulus. Stimuli include contractile activity, loading conditions, substrate supply, and environmental factors.

label.value: circadian regulation of calcium ion oscillation

value.value: Any process that modulates the concentration of cytosolic free calcium ion [Ca2+]cyt with a regularity of approximately 24 hours.

label.value: aerenchyma formation

value.value: The process that gives rise to aerenchyma, parenchyma tissue containing particularly large intercellular spaces of schizogenous or lysigenous origin. This process pertains to the initial formation of a structure from unspecified parts.

label.value: adenylate cyclase-activating glucose-activated G protein-coupled receptor signaling pathway

value.value: An adenylate cyclase-activating G protein-coupled receptor signaling pathway initiated by glucose binding to its receptor on the surface of the target cell, and ending with the regulation of a downstream cellular process.

label.value: negative regulation of transcription by transcription factor catabolism

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of DNA-dependent transcription using a mechanism that involves the catabolism of a sequence-specific DNA-binding transcription factor by hydrolysis of its peptide bonds, initiated by the covalent attachment of ubiquitin, and mediated by the proteasome.

label.value: negative regulation of transcription by transcription factor localization

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of DNA-dependent transcription using a mechanism that involves the localization of a transcription factor.

label.value: specification of ovule identity

value.value: The regionalization process in which the identity of an ovule is specified. Identity is considered to be the aggregate of characteristics by which a structure is recognized.

label.value: programmed cell death involved in cell development

value.value: The activation of endogenous cellular processes that result in the death of a cell as part of its development.

definition.value: This process is part of the natural developmental program of some cell types, but it does not always happen as part of the development or shaping of a gross anatomical structure.

label.value: regulation of Schwann cell proliferation

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency or rate of multiplication or reproduction of Schwann cells, resulting in the expansion of their population. Schwann cells are a type of glial cell in the peripheral nervous system.

label.value: positive regulation of Schwann cell proliferation

value.value: Any process that increases the frequency or rate of the multiplication or reproduction of Schwann cells, resulting in the expansion of their population. Schwann cells are a type of glial cell in the peripheral nervous system.

label.value: negative regulation of Schwann cell proliferation

value.value: Any process that decreases the frequency or extent of the multiplication or reproduction of Schwann cells, resulting in the expansion of their population. Schwann cells are a type of glial cell in the peripheral nervous system.

label.value: positive regulation of gene expression

value.value: Any process that increases the frequency, rate or extent of gene expression. Gene expression is the process in which a gene's coding sequence is converted into a mature gene product (protein or RNA).

label.value: negative regulation of gene expression

value.value: Any process that decreases the frequency, rate or extent of gene expression. Gene expression is the process in which a gene's coding sequence is converted into a mature gene product (protein or RNA).

definition.value: This term covers any process that negatively regulates the rate of production of a mature gene product, and so includes processes that negatively regulate that rate by reducing the level, stability or availability of intermediates in the process of gene expression. For example, it covers any process that reduces the level, stability or availability of mRNA or circRNA for translation and thereby reduces the rate of production of the encoded protein via translation.

label.value: regulation of transcription, start site selection

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the synthesis of either RNA on a template of DNA or DNA on a template of RNA by a mechanism that selects the start site along that template.

label.value: epithelial cell migration

value.value: The orderly movement of an epithelial cell from one site to another, often during the development of a multicellular organism.

label.value: regulation of epithelial cell migration

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of epithelial cell migration.

label.value: negative regulation of epithelial cell migration

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of epithelial cell migration.

label.value: positive regulation of epithelial cell migration

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of epithelial cell migration.

label.value: regulation of mitochondrial fusion

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of merging of two or more mitochondria within a cell to form a single compartment.

label.value: positive regulation of mitochondrial fusion

value.value: Any process that increases the frequency, rate or extent of merging of two or more mitochondria within a cell to form a single compartment.

label.value: negative regulation of mitochondrial fusion

value.value: Any process that decreases the frequency, rate or extent of merging of two or more mitochondria within a cell to form a single compartment.

label.value: positive regulation of organelle organization

value.value: Any process that increases the frequency, rate or extent of a process involved in the formation, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of an organelle.

label.value: negative regulation of organelle organization

value.value: Any process that decreases the frequency, rate or extent of a process involved in the formation, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of an organelle.

label.value: regulation of platelet-derived growth factor receptor signaling pathway

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the platelet-derived growth factor receptor signaling pathway.

label.value: positive regulation of platelet-derived growth factor receptor signaling pathway

value.value: Any process that increases the frequency, rate or extent of the platelet-derived growth factor receptor signaling pathway.

label.value: negative regulation of platelet-derived growth factor receptor signaling pathway

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the platelet-derived growth factor receptor signaling pathway.

label.value: cell communication by chemical coupling

value.value: The process that mediates signaling interactions between one cell and another cell by the transfer of small, water-soluble molecules or metabolites between their adjacent cytoplasms via intercellular protein channels.

label.value: cell communication by electrical coupling

value.value: The process that mediates signaling interactions between one cell and another cell by transfer of current between their adjacent cytoplasms via intercellular protein channels.

label.value: regulation of cell communication by chemical coupling

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of cell communication via chemical coupling. Cell communication by chemical coupling is the process that mediates signaling interactions between one cell and another cell by the transfer of small, water-soluble molecules or metabolites between their adjacent cytoplasms via intercellular protein channels.

label.value: regulation of cell communication

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of cell communication. Cell communication is the process that mediates interactions between a cell and its surroundings. Encompasses interactions such as signaling or attachment between one cell and another cell, between a cell and an extracellular matrix, or between a cell and any other aspect of its environment.

label.value: positive regulation of cell communication

value.value: Any process that increases the frequency, rate or extent of cell communication. Cell communication is the process that mediates interactions between a cell and its surroundings. Encompasses interactions such as signaling or attachment between one cell and another cell, between a cell and an extracellular matrix, or between a cell and any other aspect of its environment.
